OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F376A1782906493
OL,3,CAndy Burnham pledges more powers for
OL,4,CLondon - but who will get control?
OL,6,FHe said London's economy was
OL,7,F'overheated' and its housing market
OL,8,F'overcrowded' as he set out his vision
OL,9,Ffor the country.
OL,11,FBut London Assembly Conservative
OL,12,Fmember Neil Garratt described the plan
OL,13,Fas 'uncooked porridge', with warm
OL,14,Fwords but not much detail.
OL,16,F"If he is devolving taxes, is that
OL,17,Fextra taxes on top of everything else?
OL,18,FIf there are new powers coming to
OL,19,FLondon what are they and what are they
OL,20,Fdesigned to allow London to do?
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G2/6
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,377,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37603
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F376A1782906493
OL,3,CAndy Burnham pledges more powers for
OL,4,CLondon - but who will get control?
OL,6,F"And if it's coming to London is it
OL,7,Fcoming to the mayor or is it coming to
OL,8,Fboroughs (council leaders)?
OL,10,F"On education I don't think parents
OL,11,Fare out there thinking they want Sadiq
OL,12,FKhan to take over their school."
OL,14,FLondon has had three mayors since the
OL,15,Fjob was created in 2000 but minister
OL,16,Fare civil servants have always seemed
OL,17,Freluctant to hand over control.
OL,26,@pD@JpmpD@Zpn
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G3/6
